stories.title: West Indies v Pakistan 1999-2000
stories.subTitle: Cable & Wireless Series, 1999-2000: Third Final Match

stories.title: 3rd Final, West Indies v Pakistan, Statistical Highlights
stories.summary: It was the 1595th ODI in cricket history

stories.title: No Straight-Jacket! - Batsmen individuality respected, says Adams
stories.summary:
Port-Of-Spain - Neither Philo Wallace nor any other West Indies
batsman was given specific instructions on how to approach his
batting in the just-concluded triangular limited-overs series

stories.title: Windies make 'mush' of it
stories.summary: Port-of-Spain - While Christians around the world celebrated the resurrection of Jesus Christ, nearly 20 000 at the Queen's Park Oval and many more around the region mourned the West Indies' death in the Caribbean's first-ever triangular

stories.title: Pakistan clinch tri-series
stories.summary: Karachi, April 23: Pakistan beat the West Indies by four wickets in a low scoring thriller to clinch the tri-nation one-day series in Port-of-Spain

stories.title: Inspired bowling by Mushtaq enables Pakistan to clinch the C&W series
stories.summary:
Excellent, inspired leg-spin bowling from the obvious "Man of the
Match", Mushtaq Ahmed, who finished with 4-22, including three
wickets in one over,  enabled Pakistan to beat the West Indies in
the third and deciding one-day international final by 4
